    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of the people of the modern nation of Botswana. To refer specifically to the style and culture of the Bantu people living chiefly in Botswana and western South Africa who speak or are descendants of those who traditionally spoke the Twana dialect of the Sotho language, use "Tswana."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>現今波札那國家人民的風格與文化。若是特別指稱主要居住在波札那共和國和西南非、說著茨瓦納（Twana）方言的班圖人，或是傳統上說著茨瓦納語的人民的風格與文化，請使用「茨瓦納」一字。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stijl en cultuur van de mensen uit het moderne land Botswana. Gebruik 'Tswana' om specifiek te verwijzen naar de stijl en cultuur van de mensen van het Bantoevolk, dat hoofdzakelijk in Botswana en het westen van Zuid-Afrika leeft, die van oudsher het Twana-dialect van de Sotho-taal spreken, of die afstammen van mensen die dit dialect spraken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
